                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12588690" author="karl.wettin" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2008 19:34:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;DistanceMeasure#distance(Vector, Vector)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12588693" author="karl.wettin" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2008 19:38:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;There must be a much better solution than using a Set&amp;lt;Feature&amp;gt; as I do here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12589396" author="samee.zahur" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2008 04:25:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think what you are doing here is exactly what I tried to hide when designing VectorPair in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-34&quot; title=&quot;Iterator interface for Vectors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-34&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-34&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which basically did the same thing. (maybe the committers were hoping for a more general solution).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In any case: Say when you call calculate(vector0,vector1), feature 0 and 2 gets visited. So variables are now:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;a2 = vector0[0]^2 + vector0[2]^2
b2 = vector1[0]^2 + vector1[2]^2
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then when you call calculate(vector1,vector0), lets say feature 1 gets visited. But the method was invoked with parameters reversed, so variables now get these values:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;a2 = vector0[0]^2 + vector0[2]^2 + vector1[1]^2
b2 = vector1[0]^2 + vector1[2]^2 + vector0[1]^2
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is probably not what you had in mind.&lt;br/&gt;
This is the kind of bug you would expect to show up if we have vector0=sparsevector&lt;/p&gt;
{1,0,2}
&lt;p&gt; and vector1=sparsevector&lt;/p&gt;
{3,3,2}
&lt;p&gt;You probably expect a2=5 and b2=20, but you will get a2=14, b2=11&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12590599" author="karl.wettin" created="Fri, 18 Apr 2008 21:20:15 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is probably not what you had in mind.&lt;br/&gt;
This is the kind of bug you would expect to show up if we have vector0=sparsevector&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unknown macro: {1,0,2}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; and vector1=sparsevector&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unknown macro: {3,3,2}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You probably expect a2=5 and b2=20, but you will get a2=14, b2=11&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ahh, right. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The new patch should fix that. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
